					</svg>
					GitHub
				</a>
			</nav>
			<header>
				<span class="open-source-badge">Open Source</span>
				<span class="resource-badge">~27 MB RAM</span>
				<div class="logo">macOS Menu Bar App</div>
				<h1>AI Usage Monitor</h1>
				<p class="tagline">A native SwiftUI macOS menu bar app that shows remaining subscription usage for your AI coding tools — all in one place.</p>
			</header>

			<section class="download-section">
				<a href={downloadUrl} class="download-btn">
					<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
						<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4 16v1a3 3 0 003 3h10a3 3 0 003-3v-1m-4-4l-4 4m0 0l-4-4m4 4V4" />
					</svg>
					Download for macOS
				</a>
				<div class="app-meta">
					<span>~27 MB RAM</span>
					<span>Refreshes every 60s</span>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="screenshot-section">
				<div class="screenshot">
					<img src="/images/screenshot.png" alt="AI Usage Monitor - Main Interface" />
				</div>
				<div class="stats">
					<div class="screenshot">
						<img src="/images/cpu-usage.png" alt="CPU Usage" />
					</div>
					<div class="screenshot">
						<img src="/images/mem-usage.png" alt="Memory Usage" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="features">
				<h2>What it does</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Runs as a MenuBarExtra app with a compact SwiftUI panel</li>
					<li>Polls every 60 seconds for real-time updates</li>
					<li>Uses direct provider APIs (no interactive CLI scraping)</li>
					<li>Shows remaining quota %, reset timing, and error badges</li>
					<li>Reuses local auth context from ~/.codex and ~/.gemini</li>
					<li>Supports Claude, Gemini, Codex, Cerebras, Kimi, Minimax, and Z.AI</li>
					<li>Tiny footprint with minimal resource usage</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="providers">
				<h2>Supported Providers</h2>
				<div class="provider-grid">
					<span class="provider-badge">Claude</span>
					<span class="provider-badge">Gemini</span>
					<span class="provider-badge">Codex</span>
					<span class="provider-badge">Cerebras</span>
					<span class="provider-badge">Kimi</span>
					<span class="provider-badge">Minimax</span>
					<span class="provider-badge">Z.AI</span>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="install-guide">
				<h2>How to Install</h2>
				<div class="steps">
					<div class="step">
						<div class="step-number">1</div>
						<div class="step-content">
							<h3>Download the .dmg</h3>
							<p>Click the download button above to get the latest release.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="step">
						<div class="step-number">2</div>
						<div class="step-content">
							<h3>Open and Drag to Applications</h3>
							<p>Open the downloaded .dmg file and drag <strong>AI Usage Monitor</strong> to your Applications folder.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="step">
						<div class="step-number">3</div>
						<div class="step-content">
							<h3>Allow the App (First Launch)</h3>
							<p>Since the app is not code-signed, macOS will block it on first launch. Go to <strong>System Settings → Privacy & Security</strong> and click <strong>Open Anyway</strong>.</p>
							<div class="security-note">
								<p>This is expected behavior for unsigned apps. The app is open source and safe to use.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="security-screenshots">
						<div class="screenshot">
							<img src="/images/security.png" alt="macOS Security Warning" />
						</div>
						<div class="screenshot">
							<img src="/images/security-permission.png" alt="Open Anyway in Privacy & Security" />
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<footer>
				<a href="https://github.com/EzzatOmar/ai-usage-monitor" class="github-link">
					<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
